  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Women at least 18 years of age, who will undergo immediate unilateral or bilateral
             implant-based breast reconstruction following therapeutic skin-sparing or
             nipple-sparing mastectomy.

          2. Women at least 18 years of age, who will undergo immediate bilateral implant-based
             breast reconstruction following risk-reduction (prophylactic) skin-sparing or
             nipple-sparing mastectomy.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Subjects who are unable to read or speak English.

          2. Patients desiring autologous reconstruction.

          3. BMI &gt;40.

          4. History of radiation therapy to the breast(s), e.g. history of breast conservation
             therapy.

          5. Current nicotine and/or tobacco use.

          6. Documented diagnosis of chronic pain.

          7. Women who are pregnant or breast-feeding *

          8. Women who decline the use of acellular dermal matrix (ADM).

          9. Surgeon decision not to proceed with tissue expander reconstruction.

         10. Women undergoing single stage (straight to implant) reconstruction.
      </textblock>
